\section{conclusion}
\begin{frame}[c]\frametitle{Conclusion}
    \begin{itemize}
        \item By Using a large data set that includes 32 countries between 1976 and 2006 and a fixed effects identification strategy, they show that industries that are more dependent on external finance and that are more high-tech intensive
        exhibit a disproportionally higher innovation level in countries with better developed equity markets. However, the development of credit markets appears to discourage innovation.
        \item Economies with good growth opportunities develop financial markets to provide the funds necessary to support their good growth prospects.Simultaneity problem may still exist.

        \end{itemize}
\end{frame}
